This method checks all imports found in a specific AST node. It iterates through the list of imports and uses self._logging_modules to see if any recognized logging library was included.

```python
def visit_import(self, node):
        """Checks to see if this module uses Python's built-in logging."""
        for module, as_name in node.names:
            if module in self._logging_modules:
                self._logging_names.add(as_name or module)
```

By collecting these names into self._logging_names, other parts of your analyzer can then track usage throughout the rest of the file.
